leads.lead_text: Margins of labellum fimbriate or toothed (sometimes minutely); inner (upper) surface of labellum lamina clearly visible
Margins of labellum entire; inner surface of labellum lamina mostly or totally obscured by dorsal sepal
Labellum margin with long dark fringe
Labellum margin toothed
Labellum minutely glandular, with a purplish-red, entire boss; dorsal sepal as broad as labellum, not extending out beyond it; mostly coastal
Labellum with rough hairs, and a white, notched boss; dorsal sepal much narrower than labellum and extending out beyond it; montane forests
Dorsal sepal much reduced, less than half as wide as labellum, not hooded
Dorsal sepal broad, usually almost as wide as labellum and hooded over it
Margin of labellum incurved, forming a distinct inward-leaning rim, marginal teeth rather blunt, <1 mm long; central boss of labellum channelled at base
Margin of labellum not or barely incurved, marginal teeth acute, 1 mm long or more; central boss of labellum flat, convex or very slightly concave at base
Labellum  margin more or less erect near base and flared outward distally; rare hybrid between C. diemenicus and C. incurvus, currently only known from far south-west Victoria
Labellum margin more or less evenly flared outwards
Labellum lamina uniformly dark reddish brown, covered with short stiff hairs; auricles obscured by labellum lamina; found in Leptospermum lanigerum swamps
Labellum lamina maroon usually with a pale central boss, glabrous; auricles not obscured by labellum lamina; habitat not as above
Labellum margin flared widely; flowers >12 mm across; open forest and coastal scrub
Labellum margins flared slightly; flowers <12 mm across; mountain forests mostly on fallen logs and tree fern trunks
Dorsal sepal elliptic, strongly curved over entire labellum
Dorsal sepal broadly expanded at distal end and spoon-like, covering labellum but leaving small orifice in front
Leaf green below; labellum streaked red and white, with 5–7 rows of linear calli near orifice
Leaf red below; labellum wholly purplish, with only a central row of linear calli
